-- E.ON, Endesa Are Among 90 Bidders for Wind Parks in Spain, Cinco Reports
-- Todd White
-- 2010-07-21T06:24:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/e-on-endesa-are-among-90-bidders-for-wind-parks-in-spain-cinco-reports.html

          
          
             E.ON AG, Endesa SA, Gas Natural SGD
SA and Iberdrola SA were among 90 companies that bid to build
2,325 megawatts of wind-energy plants in the Galicia region in
northwestern Spain, Cinco Dias reported, citing unidentified
people. The investment needed by the winners will total an
estimated 3.5 billion euros ($4.5 billion), the newspaper said.
Two of largest fortunes in Galicia, those of the Manuel Jove and
Jacinto Rey families, are among investors in bidding groups, the
report said.  
          
          


  


        